data.title: Smith's Women's Track Recruiting Profile
data.meta_description: Evaluate Chelsea Owen-Smith's women's track recruiting profile. Learn how this Viewbank College student is connecting with coaches in INTERNATIONAL and nationwide.
data.text:
Personal Statement

Hi,

My name is Chelsea. I am 17 years old and I am from Viewbank College in Melbourne, Australia.

I have always loved my sports and have often made state teams for Softball and Track & Field.

I was always ok at runs and jumps but it was throwing where I found I excelled. It wasn’t until someone put a javelin in my hand that I really started to develop as an athlete.

My current best competition performances are…

158' 5" (48.17m) – Javelin 27-Mar-17

107' 11" (32.90m) – Discus (1kg)

And am currently Australian record holder for U14 Javelin (400g) and my State (Victoria) record holder for U15 & U16 Javelin. (500g) I am also currently ranked 4th in Australia in U18 in Javelin.

In the winter I play Softball for the Melbourne University Open Women Team at Short Stop, 2nd Base and relief Pitcher. The team atmosphere is quite different than Track & Field where it is an individual performance and I really love the comradery of Softball. It does help that we won our championship last season. I also use it as cross training to keep my arm turning over ready for our Summer season.

Academically I am looking at Psychology as I think mental health is extremely important. Sporting wise, I am currently training towards the Commonwealth Games in Birmingham 2022 and then Olympics 2024
